This paper discusses the technical challenges in handover parameter optimization in wireless networks, which falls under the category of network infrastructure and protocols. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also involves the analysis of probabilities and optimization, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.SY (Systems and Control). Additionally, the paper discusses the trade-off between two parameters, which could be related to security and cryptography, making cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) another possible sub-category. Finally, the paper involves the analysis of mobility management, which could be related to multimedia and human-computer interaction, making cs.MM (Multimedia) a less likely but still possible sub-category.
